com.google.appengine.googleappengine

Class GoogleAppEngine

  • java.lang.Object
    • hudson.tasks.BuildStepCompatibilityLayer
      • hudson.tasks.Builder
        • com.google.appengine.googleappengine.GoogleAppEngine
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    hudson.ExtensionPoint, hudson.model.Describable<hudson.tasks.Builder>, hudson.tasks.BuildStep, jenkins.tasks.SimpleBuildStep

    @RequiresDomain(value=Scope.class)
public class GoogleAppEngine
extends hudson.tasks.Builder
implements jenkins.tasks.SimpleBuildStep
    Sample Builder.

    When the user configures the project and enables this builder, Descriptor.newInstance(StaplerRequest) is invoked and a new GoogleAppEngine is created. The created instance is persisted to the project configuration XML by using XStream, so this allows you to use instance fields (like command) to remember the configuration.

    When a build is performed, the perform(hudson.model.AbstractBuild, hudson.Launcher, hudson.model.BuildListener) method will be invoked.

    Author:
    Kohsuke Kawaguchi
